/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/choi-vasseur-2014-decomposition.md:43:The local pressure P_{2,k} contains the same non-divergence CZ-limited term that limits beta in Vasseur (2007). CV14 simply chose not to decompose P_{2,k} further because they don't need beta > 7/6. If one further decomposed P_{2,k}, one would recover the same P_k^{21}-type bottleneck. The P_3 absorption removes terms that were ALREADY favorable in Vasseur (2007) — it is a technical convenience, not a path around the bottleneck.
